      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. but i'm looking for more than just the raw numbers. when you look at the data, some researchers argue that these disparities aren't just about socioeconomics but suggest there might be inherent cultural or even biological patterns that explain why certain groups have higher rates of specific types of offenses. can you find any literature or arguments that support that specific viewpoint for my review?",
